<subSubSection id="1C6DF74489F7FAF5ED8FED7B88F27BCC" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" type="description">
<paragraph id="0517BC662633F8EE678E82DCF635616F" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD9B42CD6C0A5BE13F7A466207038121" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">
Male 
<emphasis id="FEA2D20E7A5F57F57F42B2F15ADAB2C4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">(Holotype)</emphasis>
: total length 3.76, carapace 1.57 long, 1.42 wide (CW); abdomen 2.19 long, 1.35 wide. Eye sizes and interdistances: AME 0.09, ALE 0.11, PME 0.08, PLE 0.09; AME-AME 0.04, AME-ALE 0.01, ALE-ALE 0.23, PME-PME 0.11, PME-PLE 0.06, PLE-PLE 0.36, ALE-PLE 0.06. Eye area 0.51 wide (EAW), cephalic region 0.78 wide (CRW), EAW/CRW 0.65. CRW/CW 0.55. MOA 0.22 long, anterior width 0.22, posterior width 0.27. Clypeal height 0.09 (CH), CH/AME 1.00. Chelicerae with three promarginal (largest at middle) and two retromarginal teeth (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3A049A2A00A646A67038F020ED2533CB" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7822502" captionText="Figure 3. Male palp and chelicerae. A left palp, prolateral view; B same, retrolateral view; C Same, dorsal view; D same, ventral view; E chelicerae, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: C - conductor; E - embolus; PTA - prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA - retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD - sperm duct." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669531" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">3</figureCitation>
E). Labium 0.24 long, 0.27 wide. Sternum 0.97 long, 0.93 wide. Carapace nearly round, deep brown, with darker longitudinal markings either side of fovea. Fovea distinct, longitudinal. Abdomen grey, lacking dorsal scutum, covered with black hairs, two white patterns at middle part (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0DE6EA67DAE948D0CFB4C3ED96B0B744" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7822498" captionText="Figure 2. Habitus of Arabelia xizang sp. nov .. A Male (holotype), dorsal view; B same, ventral view; C same, abdomen dorsal view; D Female (paratype), dorsal view; E same, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669530" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">2</figureCitation>
A-C). Measurement and spines of legs as in Tables 
<tableCitation id="E36C562D38C4C5D1924552D0627F7E35" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T7822508" captionText="Table 1. Measurement of legs:" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/675989C1B9B58BE48A3FABD679073F11" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" tableUuid="675989C1B9B58BE48A3FABD679073F11">1</tableCitation>
, 
<tableCitation id="793E9C9DCB1EF8CFDF45DBF4E4897777" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="T7822509" captionText="Table 2. Spination of legs:" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/265CB41553083D61C40912B5615D4E68" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" tableUuid="265CB41553083D61C40912B5615D4E68">2</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A74E4BD463B21B558FE5C7A963FC6863" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">
Palp as in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1EA38501089DA2E206184E6975E629FF" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7822502" captionText="Figure 3. Male palp and chelicerae. A left palp, prolateral view; B same, retrolateral view; C Same, dorsal view; D same, ventral view; E chelicerae, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: C - conductor; E - embolus; PTA - prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA - retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD - sperm duct." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669531" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">3</figureCitation>
(A-D). Femur longer than tibia and cymbium, femoral apophysis absent, ventrally with low hump at distal part (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A529FAD8BD997509A0E7B6F698841888" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7822502" captionText="Figure 3. Male palp and chelicerae. A left palp, prolateral view; B same, retrolateral view; C Same, dorsal view; D same, ventral view; E chelicerae, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: C - conductor; E - embolus; PTA - prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA - retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD - sperm duct." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669531" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">3</figureCitation>
A-B). Tibia shorter than cymbium (about 0.6 times). RTA thin and short, hook-shaped (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="92A63FF52B90EC4D6D19AA6B7A8AED7A" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7822502" captionText="Figure 3. Male palp and chelicerae. A left palp, prolateral view; B same, retrolateral view; C Same, dorsal view; D same, ventral view; E chelicerae, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: C - conductor; E - embolus; PTA - prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA - retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD - sperm duct." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669531" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">3</figureCitation>
B-D). Cymbium two times longer than wide. Bulb narrower than width of cymbium. Tegulum oval, tegular apophysis absent. Sperm duct long, tapering from retrolateral to prolateral before entering base of embolus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="016FBF40DEAC05D0F2386554DD215E7B" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7822502" captionText="Figure 3. Male palp and chelicerae. A left palp, prolateral view; B same, retrolateral view; C Same, dorsal view; D same, ventral view; E chelicerae, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: C - conductor; E - embolus; PTA - prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA - retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD - sperm duct." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669531" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">3</figureCitation>
D). Embolus thin and short, directed anteriorly. Conductor membranous, originating in middle of tegulum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A8144670A19167F255D9D146A7905CA" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">
Female: One paratype total length 3.95, carapace 1.36 long, 1.24 wide (CW); abdomen 2.59 long, 1.50 wide. Eye sizes and interdistances: AME 0.08, ALE 0.09, PME 0.06, PLE 0.08; AME-AME 0.05, AME-ALE 0.01, ALE-ALE 0.20, PME-PME 0.09, PME-PLE 0.06, PLE-PLE 0.34, ALE-PLE 0.05. Eye area 0.44 wide (EAW), cephalic region 0.61 wide (CRW), EAW/CRW 0.72. CRW/CW 0.49. MOA 0.22 long, anterior width 0.19, posterior width 0.23. Clypeal height 0.07 (CH), CH/AME 0.88. Other characters as in male, except the slightly larger body size (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="61FDCEFAA013F4619C4DC9356E1D4B13" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7822498" captionText="Figure 2. Habitus of Arabelia xizang sp. nov .. A Male (holotype), dorsal view; B same, ventral view; C same, abdomen dorsal view; D Female (paratype), dorsal view; E same, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669530" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">2</figureCitation>
D-E). Measurement and spines of legs as in Tables 
<tableCitation id="4E4386C613FB971214D3207717753DC7" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T7822508" captionText="Table 1. Measurement of legs:" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/675989C1B9B58BE48A3FABD679073F11" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" tableUuid="675989C1B9B58BE48A3FABD679073F11">1</tableCitation>
, 
<tableCitation id="C12A0C744B8AD0B9455F019FD2179465" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="T7822509" captionText="Table 2. Spination of legs:" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/265CB41553083D61C40912B5615D4E68" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" tableUuid="265CB41553083D61C40912B5615D4E68">2</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F0030D851B68E6E5B54FB06D4AE54E4A" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">
Epigyne as in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="646DF73E2AAA81290C7D473AEC03C7EA" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7822506" captionText="Figure 4. Female genitalia. A Epigyne, ventral view; B Vulva, dorsal view; C Epigyne, ventral view; D Vulva, dorsal view. (A, B: cleared in pancreatin solution; C, D: macerated in Holly Oil). Abbreviations: CO - copulatory opening; CD - copulatory duct; FD - fertilisation duct; H - hood; ST 1 - primary spermatheca, ST 2 - secondary spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669532" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">4</figureCitation>
. Epigynal plate 1.3 times wider than long. MS wide. Semicircular hood located above MS (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C531E017400F9965E2E17E1CF5356BA4" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7822506" captionText="Figure 4. Female genitalia. A Epigyne, ventral view; B Vulva, dorsal view; C Epigyne, ventral view; D Vulva, dorsal view. (A, B: cleared in pancreatin solution; C, D: macerated in Holly Oil). Abbreviations: CO - copulatory opening; CD - copulatory duct; FD - fertilisation duct; H - hood; ST 1 - primary spermatheca, ST 2 - secondary spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669532" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">4</figureCitation>
A, C). Copulatory openings large, oblique, anteriorly, separated about two times MS width. Copulatory ducts short and thick. Small, globular ST2 located at middle parts, kidney-shaped ST1 posterior (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="039543AECAF5D80E9A707099D9288B80" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7822506" captionText="Figure 4. Female genitalia. A Epigyne, ventral view; B Vulva, dorsal view; C Epigyne, ventral view; D Vulva, dorsal view. (A, B: cleared in pancreatin solution; C, D: macerated in Holly Oil). Abbreviations: CO - copulatory opening; CD - copulatory duct; FD - fertilisation duct; H - hood; ST 1 - primary spermatheca, ST 2 - secondary spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669532" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">4</figureCitation>
B). Fertilisation ducts downwards, located posteriorly of spermathecae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BEF8F977F15D0CF13685DB4533AD5A7C" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7822506" captionText="Figure 4. Female genitalia. A Epigyne, ventral view; B Vulva, dorsal view; C Epigyne, ventral view; D Vulva, dorsal view. (A, B: cleared in pancreatin solution; C, D: macerated in Holly Oil). Abbreviations: CO - copulatory opening; CD - copulatory duct; FD - fertilisation duct; H - hood; ST 1 - primary spermatheca, ST 2 - secondary spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669532" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">4</figureCitation>
B, D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6D92E2858B89432C757462CD80086E5C" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FEB327343CEB456CAA245657B1B2AD04" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="37D9819B498E45A9F4C30736F5470AD5" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">
This new species is similar to the type species 
<taxonomicName id="4552CE90405AADB270FB9FA11B7E7A18" genus="A." lsidName="A. pheidoleicomes" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" rank="species" species="pheidoleicomes">
<emphasis id="0377FDF9DE25C1E682F040492A8509A0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">A. pheidoleicomes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bosselaers, 2009 in having similar-shaped palp in the male, the position of copulatory openings and the presence of an anterior hood in the female. However, it can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="EF998DBB2F13897FBD85022BCEA7EB4E" genus="A." lsidName="A. pheidoleicomes" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" rank="species" species="pheidoleicomes">
<emphasis id="E5D9B6D702C8932A8381809E9E7B1112" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">A. pheidoleicomes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bosselaers, 2009 by: 1) the hook-shaped RTA (vs. straight, compare Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CFB0D0650DB97F0EBAB91B684520E334" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7822502" captionText="Figure 3. Male palp and chelicerae. A left palp, prolateral view; B same, retrolateral view; C Same, dorsal view; D same, ventral view; E chelicerae, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: C - conductor; E - embolus; PTA - prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA - retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD - sperm duct." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669531" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">3</figureCitation>
C and Fig. 15 in 
<bibRefCitation id="06960DA8EBBB27DBC2080F6E611BA7CF" author="Bosmans, R." journalOrPublisher="Arachnologische Mitteilungen" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" pagination="15 - 22" refId="B7822442" refString="Bosmans, R., 2011. On some new or rare spider species from Lesbos, Greece (Araneae: Agelenidae, Amaurobiidae, Corinnidae, Gnaphosidae, Liocranidae). Arachnologische Mitteilungen 40: 15 - 22" title="On some new or rare spider species from Lesbos, Greece (Araneae: Agelenidae, Amaurobiidae, Corinnidae, Gnaphosidae, Liocranidae)." volume="40" year="2011">Bosmans 2011</bibRefCitation>
); 2) the slightly curved embolus(vs. straight, compare Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C5D57B60F3BF9500A0D36F6D5432F5D9" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7822502" captionText="Figure 3. Male palp and chelicerae. A left palp, prolateral view; B same, retrolateral view; C Same, dorsal view; D same, ventral view; E chelicerae, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: C - conductor; E - embolus; PTA - prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA - retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD - sperm duct." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669531" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">3</figureCitation>
D and Fig. 16 in 
<bibRefCitation id="F27B00A0CD88191504EF43787DF6491C" author="Bosmans, R." journalOrPublisher="Arachnologische Mitteilungen" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" pagination="15 - 22" refId="B7822442" refString="Bosmans, R., 2011. On some new or rare spider species from Lesbos, Greece (Araneae: Agelenidae, Amaurobiidae, Corinnidae, Gnaphosidae, Liocranidae). Arachnologische Mitteilungen 40: 15 - 22" title="On some new or rare spider species from Lesbos, Greece (Araneae: Agelenidae, Amaurobiidae, Corinnidae, Gnaphosidae, Liocranidae)." volume="40" year="2011">Bosmans 2011</bibRefCitation>
), 3) a large, wide and sclerotised hood (vs. small, compare Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E5C392EB065C9A8C2448FE64D4B5AF4A" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7822506" captionText="Figure 4. Female genitalia. A Epigyne, ventral view; B Vulva, dorsal view; C Epigyne, ventral view; D Vulva, dorsal view. (A, B: cleared in pancreatin solution; C, D: macerated in Holly Oil). Abbreviations: CO - copulatory opening; CD - copulatory duct; FD - fertilisation duct; H - hood; ST 1 - primary spermatheca, ST 2 - secondary spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669532" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">4</figureCitation>
A and Fig. 7F in 
<bibRefCitation id="B9F31EF5AB383E8E06D61DD26731D533" author="Bosselaers, J." journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" pagination="37 - 55" refId="B7822433" refString="Bosselaers, J., 2009. Studies in Liocranidae (Araneae): redescriptions and transfers in Apostenus Westring and Brachyanillus Simon, as well as description of a new genus. Zootaxa 2141: 37 - 55" title="Studies in Liocranidae (Araneae): redescriptions and transfers in Apostenus Westring and Brachyanillus Simon, as well as description of a new genus." volume="2141" year="2009">Bosselaers 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and 4) the kidney-shaped spermathecae (vs. round, compare Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9E470E5A57082628583D04AFE17823A8" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7822506" captionText="Figure 4. Female genitalia. A Epigyne, ventral view; B Vulva, dorsal view; C Epigyne, ventral view; D Vulva, dorsal view. (A, B: cleared in pancreatin solution; C, D: macerated in Holly Oil). Abbreviations: CO - copulatory opening; CD - copulatory duct; FD - fertilisation duct; H - hood; ST 1 - primary spermatheca, ST 2 - secondary spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669532" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">4</figureCitation>
B and Fig. 7E in 
<bibRefCitation id="87636B4187E11526B424EE2BCE79B582" author="Bosselaers, J." journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" pagination="37 - 55" refId="B7822433" refString="Bosselaers, J., 2009. Studies in Liocranidae (Araneae): redescriptions and transfers in Apostenus Westring and Brachyanillus Simon, as well as description of a new genus. Zootaxa 2141: 37 - 55" title="Studies in Liocranidae (Araneae): redescriptions and transfers in Apostenus Westring and Brachyanillus Simon, as well as description of a new genus." volume="2141" year="2009">Bosselaers 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="07090F1AA594C009E9A7C7791B51FA5D" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="F30FFDED6317ECE3237776F4546CEBF6" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">Etymology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C8C50BE60B9F891C3B8D97702FEDD641" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">The specific name is derived from the type locality; noun.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="674D2F10DB5F5459C278F6D53C01D4AE" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D0A16B7CBB4AC7186BB03746F3105121" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1E381C3A965769AFA184CA760AE5039E" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">Known only from the type locality (China: Xizang).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BB8F77D60615E6BFFC781EF38F4E2BB0" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" type="notes">
<paragraph id="460593594394C2553B2D3F7C3BC9FF06" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="26CCD2E920F8C53D213B54B8933792D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">
The spiders of this new species are found under stones on the side of roads (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="18E6AB944F31DA4E548271D667B0D7DC" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7822494" captionText="Figure 1. Habitat and female of Arabelia xizang sp. nov .. A habitat; B living image (Photograph by Yannan Mu)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669528" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">1</figureCitation>
A). Female matured about half a month earlier than male (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5268D5E35AAF51A7E9DBD4F0DFF69B5A" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7822494" captionText="Figure 1. Habitat and female of Arabelia xizang sp. nov .. A habitat; B living image (Photograph by Yannan Mu)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85436.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669528" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">1</figureCitation>
B). We collected the adult females and subadult male, the male description being based on the adult reared from the subadult.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F57E953199143C2BD33D4C478B1EE10D" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">
According to Bosselaers (2009), the type species of 
<taxonomicName id="C4F36979C5E5D2A4A6B8053A4C4E06AC" authorityName="Bosselaers" authorityYear="2009" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Arabelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Arabelia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C2EA83F6B934D7ACCAB3C19ABE64551A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">Arabelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
show clear myrmecophily, but we did not find ants or termites when collecting this new species under gravel. Moreover, there are also differences in the colour between 
<taxonomicName id="46708169FC36F6107AB6C0274DB3E0EE" genus="A." lsidName="A. pheidoleicomes" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" rank="species" species="pheidoleicomes">
<emphasis id="3B8A03A9FEBC14D620B6B0D3674B8602" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">A. pheidoleicomes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="52E563AA91684E47F3AA699D98ED4876" genus="A." lsidName="A. xizang" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" rank="species" species="xizang">
<emphasis id="0C959D003BFF02C187108E8102835B86" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">A. xizang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="AB61ACD5042DF6435887A3CAB5CAAE3B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">sp. n.</emphasis>
in the natural state and in alcohol. The former species has brown carapace, grey abdomen in the natural state and yellow carapace, white abdomen in alcohol, while the new species is black in the natural state and has brown carapace and grey abdomen in alcohol. However, due to its similar genital characters, we placed this new species in 
<taxonomicName id="257E23501C77273A6EE5F64FABDD75BC" authorityName="Bosselaers" authorityYear="2009" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Arabelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Arabelia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="26DACB3575EDA927DA5B95D03BAC15EC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85436">Arabelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
